@startuml refresh-logout-flow

title Token Refresh (Cookie-based) & Logout

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 8

actor       "User"                as user
participant "Angular Interceptor" as inter  #LightGray
participant "AuthController"      as ctrl   #LightBlue
participant "KeycloakAuthService" as svc    #LightBlue
participant "Keycloak"            as kc     #LightGreen

== Silent Token Refresh (triggered by 401 or proactive on expiry) ==

note over inter
  Browser sends refresh_token cookie automatically.
  Angular never reads it — it's HttpOnly.
end note

inter -> ctrl : POST /api/auth/refresh\nCookie: refresh_token=<value>\n(no body needed for RT)

ctrl  -> svc  : refresh(cookie RT)
svc   -> kc   : POST /token\ngrant_type=refresh_token\nrefresh_token=<value>

alt refresh token valid
    kc    --> svc  : { access_token, refresh_token, expires_in }

    note over ctrl
      Backend rotates both tokens:
      - new refresh_token → Set-Cookie (replaces old)
      - new access_token  → response body
    end note

    ctrl  --> inter : 200 OK\nSet-Cookie: refresh_token=...; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict\n{ access_token, expires_in }
    inter --> inter : updates AT in memory\nretries original request

else refresh token expired / revoked
    kc    --> svc  : 400 { error: invalid_grant }
    svc   --> ctrl : throws KeycloakAuthException
    ctrl  --> inter : 401
    inter --> user  : redirect to login\n(session fully expired)
end

== Logout ==

user  -> inter : clicks logout
inter -> ctrl  : POST /api/auth/logout\nCookie: refresh_token=<value>

ctrl  -> svc   : logout(cookie RT)
svc   -> kc    : POST /revoke\ntoken=<refresh_token>

kc    --> svc  : 200 OK
note right of kc
  Keycloak 26 always returns 200.
  Token is invalidated server-side.
end note

ctrl  --> inter : 200 OK\nSet-Cookie: refresh_token=; Max-Age=0 (clears cookie)

note over inter
  Angular clears AT from memory.
  Cookie cleared by Set-Cookie: Max-Age=0.
  Redirect to login page.
end note

inter --> user  : logged out

@enduml
